2026-04-14 | Minimum Total Distance for Robots to Factories

Question:
•	You have robots on a line and factories with capacities.  
•	Each robot must go to **one factory**.  
•	Each factory can repair limited robots.  

•	Cost:
		distance = |robot position - factory position|  

•	Goal:
		assign robots to factories such that:
		total distance is minimized.

	Key Idea
This is a **minimum cost assignment with capacity constraints**.  
After sorting, optimal assignment happens in order.

	Approach
1.	Sort robots  
2.	Sort factories by position  

3.	Use DP:
		dp[i][j] =
			min cost to assign first i robots using first j factories  

4.	Transition:
		For each factory j:
			try assigning k robots (0 to limitj)

5.	Cost calculation:
		sum of distances of assigned robots  

	Time Complexity
	O(n × m × limit)

	Space Complexity
	O(n × m)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    long long minimumTotalDistance(vector<int>& robot,
                                   vector<vector<int>>& factory) {

        sort(robot.begin(), robot.end());
        sort(factory.begin(), factory.end());

        int n = robot.size();
        int m = factory.size();

        vector<vector<long long>> dp(n+1, vector<long long>(m+1, LLONG_MAX));

        for(int j=0;j<=m;j++) dp[0][j] = 0;

        for(int j=1;j<=m;j++){

            int pos = factory[j-1][0];
            int limit = factory[j-1][1];

            for(int i=0;i<=n;i++){

                // case: don't use this factory
                dp[i][j] = dp[i][j-1];

                long long cost = 0;

                for(int k=1;k<=limit && k<=i;k++){

                    cost += abs(robot[i-k] - pos);

                    if(dp[i-k][j-1] != LLONG_MAX){
                        dp[i][j] = min(dp[i][j],
                                       dp[i-k][j-1] + cost);
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        return dp[n][m];
    }
};

	Key Insight
After sorting:
optimal matching is **sequential (no crossing assignments)**  

So we can:
- assign robots in order  
- distribute them across factories using DP  

This converts a complex matching problem into structured DP.
